Xeroderma Pigmentosum (XP) is a rare genetic disorder characterized by extreme sensitivity to ultraviolet (UV) rays from sunlight. The need for effective treatment options for XP patients has led to the development of various segments within the Xeroderma Pigmentosum Treatment Market. One key segment is the treatment type, which includes drugs, photoprotection measures, and surgical treatment options. Drugs play a crucial role in managing XP symptoms and preventing skin cancer development. Photoprotection methods such as clothing and sunscreens are essential in minimizing UV exposure, while surgical treatments like skin grafting are used in severe cases to repair damaged skin. Another vital segment is the end-user category, encompassing hospitals for intensive care, clinics for regular treatment and follow-ups, and research institutes for new therapy developments and clinical trials.

